Object.Field:
Schedule this scenario hourly with 4 repetitions every 15 minutes. The Scenario will provide itself to raise an error if it is already running
Execute this script on the desired Schema (Default is INT_STD but you can choose NICIM or EPMASTER).
Change the Logical Schema property according to the Physical Schema (Default is SQLSERVER_INTERFACCIA but you can change it to SQLSERVER_NICIM or SQLSERVER_EPMASTER) in these objects:
A. WAIT FOR DATA
B. ORACLE_START_SCENERY 1. Set Start Value (Source and Target Command) 2. Execute Scenery (Source Command) 3. Set End Value (Target Command)
TEST Script:
CREATE TABLE ETL_SCENERY_EXECUTION ( "SCEN_NAME" VARCHAR(200) NOT NULL, "SCEN_VERSION" VARCHAR(35) DEFAULT '001' NOT NULL, "CONTEXT" VARCHAR(35) DEFAULT 'TEST' NOT NULL, "AGENT_CODE" VARCHAR(35) DEFAULT 'AGENT' NOT NULL, "FLG_EXEC" DECIMAL(38,0) DEFAULT 1 NOT NULL, "STATUS" VARCHAR(35) DEFAULT 'In attesa' NOT NULL, "PRIORITY" DECIMAL(38,0) DEFAULT 0 NOT NULL, "SYNC_MODE" DECIMAL(38,0) DEFAULT 1 NOT NULL, "START_DATE" DATETIME, "END_DATE" DATETIME, CONSTRAINT "ODI_SCENERY_EXECUTION_PK" PRIMARY KEY ("SCEN_NAME", "SCEN_VERSION", "CONTEXT", "AGENT_CODE"));
PROD Script:
CREATE TABLE ETL_SCENERY_EXECUTION ( "SCEN_NAME" VARCHAR(200) NOT NULL, "SCEN_VERSION" VARCHAR(35) DEFAULT '001' NOT NULL, "CONTEXT" VARCHAR(35) DEFAULT 'PROD' NOT NULL, "AGENT_CODE" VARCHAR(35) DEFAULT 'AGENT' NOT NULL, "FLG_EXEC" DECIMAL(38,0) DEFAULT 1 NOT NULL, "STATUS" VARCHAR(35) DEFAULT 'In attesa' NOT NULL, "PRIORITY" DECIMAL(38,0) DEFAULT 0 NOT NULL, "SYNC_MODE" DECIMAL(38,0) DEFAULT 1 NOT NULL, "START_DATE" DATETIME, "END_DATE" DATETIME, CONSTRAINT "ODI_SCENERY_EXECUTION_PK" PRIMARY KEY ("SCEN_NAME", "SCEN_VERSION", "CONTEXT", "AGENT_CODE"));
Synchronization mode of the scenario:
1 - Synchronous mode (default). The execution of the calling session is blocked until the scenario finishes its execution.
2 - Asynchronous mode. The execution of the calling session continues independently from the return of the called scenario. -SCEN_STATUS=VALID
SELECT COUNT(*) FROM <?=odiRef.getObjectName("SNP_SESSION") ?> WHERE SESS_NAME = '<?=odiRef.getSession("SESS_NAME") ?>' AND SESS_STATUS='R'
SELECT SCEN_NAME, SCEN_VERSION, CONTEXT, AGENT_CODE FROM (SELECT TOP 1 * FROM <?=odiRef.getObjectName("ETL_SCENERY_EXECUTION") ?> WHERE FLG_EXEC=0 ORDER BY PRIORITY ASC) FIRST

UPDATE <?=odiRef.getObjectName("ETL_SCENERY_EXECUTION") ?> SET START_DATE=GETDATE() , STATUS='Executing', FLG_EXEC=2 WHERE SCEN_NAME='#SCEN_NAME' AND SCEN_VERSION='#SCEN_VERSION' AND CONTEXT='#CONTEXT' AND AGENT_CODE='#AGENT_CODE'
SELECT SCEN_NAME, SCEN_VERSION, CONTEXT, AGENT_CODE, SYNC_MODE FROM <?=odiRef.getObjectName("ETL_SCENERY_EXECUTION") ?> WHERE FLG_EXEC=2
UPDATE <?=odiRef.getObjectName("ETL_SCENERY_EXECUTION") ?> SET END_DATE=GETDATE(), STATUS='Waiting for update', FLG_EXEC=1 WHERE FLG_EXEC =2
UPDATE <?=odiRef.getObjectName("SNP_SESSION") ?> set SESS_BEG = dateadd(minute, -1, getdate()), SESS_END = dateadd(minute, -1, getdate()) where SESS_BEG is null
